Welcome to PyCon India 2021, the premier Python conference in India, organized by the community, for the community.

The conference will be kicking off September 18th, 12:00 IST (UTC+5:30) with the opening address. Join us for the event on Hopin using <this link>. You can find the updated schedule on the Hopin event page at all times. Don't forget to join our communication platform [Zulip](https://pyconindia.zulipchat.com/join/mtuwo5arpwiptpzdmoyd5jdv/) to connect and network with other conference attendees and speakers.

On our first day, we will be having 25+ talks, Neurodiversity sessions, Birds of a Feather (BoF) sessions, panel discussions, lightning talks, and much more. You can read more about the conference in the [PyCon India Program Guide](https://in.pycon.org/share/PyConIndia2021ProgramGuide.pdf). You can generate your [conference badge](https://in.pycon.org/badges/) which you can edit as per your liking and share it with your friends.

If you are looking for help, then reach out to `2021/helpdesk` Zulip stream or the helpdesk in Hopin. If you have any questions or want to know more about something. Please make sure you follow the conference, [Code of Conduct](https://in.pycon.org/2021/coc/) to make the conference a great experience for everyone.

Looking forward to meeting you at the conference.

Regards,
PyCon India 2021 Team
